HEADWORD: Terraqueous
<hw>Ter*ra"que*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>terra</ets> the earth + E. <ets>aqueous</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Consisting of land and water; <as>as, the earth is a
<ex>terraqueous</ex> globe</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The grand <qex>terraqueous</qex> spectacle⟦br⟧
